briefdescription.para: Only fields with a Pack Attribute will be included.
The default PackAttribute will be applied to all recognized public fields.
Indicates what automatically will be Packed.
For PackObjects this uses the default of State.

detaileddescription.para: For Pack syncvar fields this indicates they should use the PackObject setting.

briefdescription.para: Pack syncvar replicates changes in value to other clients, and stays at that value until changed by the owner.
Pack syncvar resets value on owner after its value is captured/sent.

detaileddescription.para: Reset is done with value = new T(). Only works on struct types.

briefdescription.para: Callbacks assigned to Pack attributes can be called before or after the value is set.

detaileddescription.para: You can also opt for the value not to be automatically set at all, and handle it yourself in the callback;

briefdescription.para: This enum indicates if an extra bit should be added to indicate cases of Zero value.

detaileddescription.para: When value is zero, only the one bit is sent. Useful for values that spend more time at zero than not, and delta frames are not an option.

briefdescription.para: This enum indicates if an extra bit should be added to indicate cases of Zero value, XXXXX preValue, or two bits should be added to indicate Zero, Min, Max.

detaileddescription.para: When value is one of those, only the indicator bits will be written. Use this if these values are expected to spend most of their life at zero, min or max.
